The paper focuses on a neurorobotic experiment involving an iCub robot, which suggests that it belongs to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The experiment involves processing stereophonic sound, facial features, and body motion, which suggests that it may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SD) sub-categories. The paper proposes a deep learning model, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
